description.narrative:
Reprogrammed funds to address COVID-19
Oxfam has applied to Sida for funding of 52 901 215 SEK to carry out the "Governance and Community Protection Program 2018-2022-  our rights our duties in DRC" during the period 2018-2022.

The program aims to advance the goal of a DRC in which women and men, civil society organizations, and community groups are able to exercise their rights, secure protection from violence and abuse, voice priorities, and participate in decisions that affect their lives. 

The program will :
•	Enable communities, local public institutions and CSOs to adopt new or change current practices and attitudes to increase respect for human rights and women’s rights, and reduce discrimination and violence; 

•	Support community-level governance committees, including women’s forums, to build the capacity and confidence for collective action that engages territorial and provincial authorities to improve the accountability of governance, respect for gender equality and effectiveness of protection processes; 

•	Establish and facilitate a citizen-state consultation process by which authorities at provincial, territorial and local levels adopt practices and procedures in response to citizens’ demands for increased accountability, transparency, inclusiveness of governance, increased respect for gender equality and increased protection of citizens’ rights; 

•	Strengthen the capacity of national advocacy organizations to apply an evidence-based approach that represents the views and incorporates the testimonies drawn directly from local civil society organizations and ordinary citizens, to be more effective and credible in their advocacy efforts.

Oxfam will implement the intervention together with the local organizations in three DRC provinces namely: Equateur, South Kivu and Tanganyika.  The intervention’s total budget is 52 901 215 SEK and Sida is the only donor to the program.
